---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="1v1 Structure">
  <main class="design-essay">
    
    <header class="essay-header">
      <span class="super-title">Design Philosophy III</span>
      <h1>1v1 Structure</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Magic in its Original Form</p>
    </header>

    <hr />

    <article class="prose-block">
      <p class="lead-paragraph">
        Tiny Leaders Reborn is designed from the ground up as a one-on-one format. 1v1 play is the game’s 
        original form and TLR embraces that structure, allowing it to inform how decks are built, how games 
        progress, and how players approach each decision.
      </p>
    </article>

    <section class="chapter-section">
      <div class="prose-block">
        <h3>The Unambiguous Objective</h3>
        <p>
          In a 1v1 environment, the objective is unambiguous. A player must defeat the opponent across the 
          table. There are no shifting alliances, no shared threats, and no table politics to absorb pressure 
          or redistribute responsibility.
        </p>
        <div class="focus-box">
          <p>
            Every spell, attack, and interaction is aimed at a single opponent who is actively contesting 
            your plan. That clarity produces a level of focus and tension that multiplayer formats simply 
            don’t provide.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="chapter-section alt-bg">
      <div class="prose-block">
        <h3>Removing the Safety Valves</h3>
        <p>
          Multiplayer Commander often rewards patience and positioning, waiting for openings, leveraging 
          diplomacy, or letting the table correct imbalances. In 1v1, those safety valves disappear.
        </p>
        <ul class="contrast-list">
          <li>Pressure must be applied proactively.</li>
          <li>Threats must be answered directly.</li>
          <li>Closing a game is your responsibility alone.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Errors are punished more quickly, and advantages are something you establish and maintain, 
          not something you can negotiate away.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="chapter-section">
      <div class="prose-block">
        <h3>Sharper Play</h3>
        <p>
          This structure naturally incentivizes sharper play, even when decks themselves are not fully 
          optimized. Pacing, resource management, and inevitability matter from the opening turns. 
          Interaction becomes more purposeful, and strategies must function without assuming additional 
          opponents or extended setup windows.
        </p>
        <p>
          Importantly, 1v1 does not narrow expression, rather it refines it. Creativity still thrives, 
          but expectations shift. Decks are built to engage an opponent head-on, whether through focused 
          execution, disruption, or prolonged interactive play. With multiplayer dynamics removed, those 
          choices resolve more cleanly and carry more weight.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <footer class="essay-footer prose-block">
      <p>
        By committing to a 1v1 identity, Tiny Leaders Reborn roots itself in Magic’s most direct form 
        of play while clearly distinguishing itself from multiplayer Commander. The result is a format 
        defined by clarity, agency, and intentional interaction.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>TLR is designed so that every match is a contest between two players, and every outcome is earned turn by turn.</strong>
      </p>
    </footer>

    <nav class="series-nav">
      
      <a href="/design/commander-variant" class="nav-card prev">
        <span class="nav-label">Previous</span>
        <div class="nav-inner">
          <span class="nav-arrow">&larr;</span>
          <span class="chapter-title">A Commander Variant</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/design/maindeck" class="nav-card next">
        <span class="nav-label">Next Element</span>
        <div class="nav-inner">
          <span class="chapter-title">Deck Size</span>
          <span class="nav-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>

    </nav>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* --- REUSING DESIGN SYSTEM STYLES --- */
  .design-essay {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1rem;
    color: var(--text-body);
  }

  .prose-block {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  /* --- HEADER --- */
  .essay-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .super-title {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: bold;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .essay-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--heading-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .lead-paragraph {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--heading-color);
  }

  /* --- SECTIONS --- */
  .chapter-section {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .chapter-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: var(--heading-color);
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* --- FOCUS BOX (New for this page) --- */
  .focus-box {
    border-top: 2px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding: 2rem 0;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--heading-color);
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* --- CONTRAST LIST (New for this page) --- */
  .contrast-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .contrast-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: var(--heading-color);
  }

  .contrast-list li::before {
    content: "!";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 900;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  /* --- ALT BACKGROUND --- */
  .alt-bg {
    background-color: var(--surface);
    margin-left: calc(-50vw + 50%);
    margin-right: calc(-50vw + 50%);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    padding-right: 1rem;
    width: 100vw;
  }

  /* --- NAVIGATION --- */
  .series-nav {
    margin-top: 6rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .nav-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-decoration: none;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 300px;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .nav-card:hover {
    background-color: var(--surface);
    border-color: var(--border-subtle);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .nav-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .prev { align-items: flex-start; text-align: left; }
  .next { align-items: flex-end; text-align: right; }

  .nav-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .chapter-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: var(--heading-color);
  }

  .nav-arrow {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* Mobile Fix */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .alt-bg {
      margin-left: -1rem;
      margin-right: -1rem;
      width: calc(100% + 2rem);
    }
    
    .series-nav {
      flex-direction: column; 
      gap: 2rem;
    }
    
    .nav-card {
      max-width: 100%;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
      background-color: var(--surface);
      border-color: var(--border-subtle);
    }
    
    .prev, .next { align-items: center; text-align: center; }
  }
</style>